    content: [
      'A workflow does not drift only because the tool is weak. It drifts because the handoff is thin.',
      'That is where many AI-assisted systems quietly lose operating value. A call is summarized, a proposal is drafted, a content brief is generated, a lead is scored, or a customer issue is routed. The output looks useful. But the next person receives only the artifact, not the context needed to trust, correct, act on, or improve it.',
      'Kramaniti&apos;s homepage starts with business reality: workflows, handoffs, bottlenecks, decisions, people, and priorities. It then moves into intelligence systems and finally into brand presence. Handoff debt sits between those layers. If context does not travel cleanly from one step to the next, intelligence stays scattered and presence starts repeating claims the operation cannot inspect.',
      '[Inference] AI drift is often handoff debt with a more fluent surface. The team is not only checking whether the model wrote a good sentence or picked the right label. It is checking whether the operating context survived the move from one person, system, or stage to another.',
      '[infographic:handoff-packet-map]',
      '<h3>The Handoff Packet Should Be Smaller Than The Workflow</h3>',
      'A handoff packet is not a full process manual. It is the minimum context the next owner needs in order to continue the work without reopening the whole history.',
      '[Fact] IHI&apos;s SBAR tool frames critical communication around Situation, Background, Assessment, and Recommendation. It describes SBAR as a concrete mechanism for setting expectations about what will be communicated between team members.',
      '[Inference] Kramaniti&apos;s domain is not clinical care, but the operating principle transfers cleanly: a useful handoff separates the current situation, the relevant background, the owner&apos;s assessment, and the requested next action. Without those fields, the next person receives activity without enough judgment.',
      '[Recommendation] For one commercial workflow, define six handoff fields: trigger, context source, current status, decision boundary, next owner, and write-back location. If a field is blank, the workflow is asking someone to reconstruct intelligence from memory.',
      '<h3>Process Maps Need Message Flow, Not Only Task Flow</h3>',
      'Many operating maps show the steps but not the context that crosses between them. That is why a workflow can look tidy while still failing in daily use. The sequence says what happens next; the handoff says what must travel for the next step to be reliable.',
      '[Fact] OMG&apos;s BPMN 2.0.2 specification is a formal standard for Business Process Model and Notation. Its collaboration model includes participants, lanes, message flows, conversations, and data elements, which makes the interaction between actors part of the model rather than a note outside it.',
      '[Inference] A founder-led brand can borrow the discipline without adopting enterprise modeling ceremony. When a lead moves from discovery to proposal, or a content idea moves from internal signal to public article, the map should show the message, source record, owner, exception route, and accepted output.',
      '[Recommendation] Before building a dashboard, automation, or AI support layer, map one handoff in plain language. Who starts it? What record travels? What question is being answered? Who can approve or reject the output? Where does the accepted version return?',
      '[infographic:handoff-trace-route]',
      '<h3>Traces Are A Useful Analogy For Business Workflows</h3>',
      '[Fact] OpenTelemetry describes spans as units of work that become the building blocks of traces. Its trace documentation explains that context propagation lets spans be correlated and assembled into a trace even when they are generated in different places.',
      '[Inference] The business lesson is simple: if a workflow crosses tools, people, or stages, the context needs a way to travel. Otherwise the organization sees isolated outputs instead of a connected route.',
      'For Kramaniti&apos;s work, that might mean a discovery-call insight keeps its source link when it becomes a proposal line. A proposal exception keeps its owner and reason when it becomes an operating rule. A content claim keeps its source boundary when it becomes a public article. The point is not technical observability for its own sake. The point is retained operating context.',
      '<h3>The Human Owner Still Carries Judgment</h3>',
      'A handoff packet should not make the system look more certain than it is. It should show where judgment remains human-led.',
      'If AI summarizes a sales call, the packet should say who accepted the summary. If AI drafts a customer reply, it should say what condition requires human review. If AI clusters content ideas, it should say which claims are only internal signals and which have enough source support for public communication.',
      '[Recommendation] Treat every AI-assisted handoff as a responsibility boundary. The system may draft, classify, retrieve, or route. A person still owns the standard, the exception, the promise, and the final record when trust, taste, pricing, privacy, or public claims are involved.',
      '<h3>Presence Fails When The Handoff Cannot Be Replayed</h3>',
      'The external communication layer depends on the same handoff discipline. A website line, founder post, sales note, or Insights article should not ask the reader to trust a polished sentence detached from the route that produced it.',
      'When a handoff can be replayed, the brand can communicate with more confidence and less hype. The business can see where the signal appeared, which record supported it, who interpreted it, what boundary protected the claim, and what changed after publication.',
      '[Recommendation] Start with the workflow that already creates the most correction: lead qualification, proposal scoping, onboarding, reporting, content approval, customer follow-up, or internal tool support. Write the handoff packet for that route before adding more AI capability.',
      'Handoff debt shows up as AI drift because intelligence cannot become infrastructure unless context survives the move. Build the packet first. Then let the system assist inside a route the business can inspect, teach, and improve.',
    ],
